{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":35251,"record_hash":"sha256:70bcea92a23056819fa834199db245984427ef3e952b5ca2071a37f55d9632ec","timestamp":"2026-05-11T20:24:51.765Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"Found it. The second sync was slow because GitMeta was still serializing local metadata even when the local and remote metadata refs already matched. With ~31 MB of transcript list payload, that made a no-op sync do expensive local work.\n\nI fixed this in `/Users/kiril/src/git-meta` by making `push_once()` skip serialization when there is already a local metadata ref and the SQLite store has no changes since the last materialization. Then I temporarily pointed `but-agentlog` at the local GitMeta checkout so `target/debug/but` uses the fix.\n\nTiming on this repo:\n\n```text\nbefore: ~11.15s\nafter first rebuilt sync: ~3.79s\nafter repeated no-op sync: ~1.80s\n```\n\nThe remaining ~1.8s is mostly the GitHub remote check/fetch over SSH.\n\nValidation passed:\n```text\ncargo test -p git-meta-lib clean_store_with_local_ref_does_not_need_serialization\ncargo test -p but-agentlog\ncargo check -p but --features agentlog\ncargo clippy -p git-meta-lib --all-targets --no-deps\ncargo clippy -p but-agentlog --all-targets --no-deps\n```\n\nOne note: `crates/but-agentlog/Cargo.toml` is now using the local GitMeta path. Once we publish the GitMeta fix, we should switch it back to a pinned GitHub SHA.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-11T20:24:51.765Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}